# Build & git

## Stack

Paper **26.1.2**, Java **25**, Maven shade → RPG JAR.

Maven: `C:\Users\Danie\tools\apache-maven-3.9.10\bin\mvn.cmd`

## Two repositories

| Project | Path | Output |
|---------|------|--------|
| Civs Custom | `../Civs-1.11.6/` | `target/civs-1.11.6.jar` |
| RPG Server | `rpg-server-plugin/` | `target/rpg-server-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar` |

Build Civs first when RPG needs updated Civs JAR (`system` scope in `pom.xml`).

Both repos may be edited. Deploy **both** JARs to Linux server `plugins/`.

## Commands

```powershell
& "C:\Users\Danie\tools\apache-maven-3.9.10\bin\mvn.cmd" -f "..\Civs-1.11.6\pom.xml" compile
& "C:\Users\Danie\tools\apache-maven-3.9.10\bin\mvn.cmd" compile
```

## Git

- Separate commits per logical fix/feature; imperative message.
- Run `mvn compile` (or `mvn test`) before push.
- Commit `.cursor/skills/` and `.cursor/rules/`; do not commit other `.cursor/` state.
- Do **not** commit `../reference-plugins/` (local study clones).

